clinical program the stanford center for sleep sciences and medicine stanford university school of medicine stanford school of medicine the stanford center for sleep sciences and medicine search this site only stanford medical sites ways to give find a person alumni lane library ways to give find a person clinical program founded in the early 1970s by drs william dement and christian guilleminault the stanford university sleep disorders clinic was the first medical clinic ever established to specialize in sleep disorders the clinic diagnoses and treats patients who have difficulties falling asleep or staying asleep at night problems with excessive daytime sleepiness or other medical problems occurring during sleep there are also specialized clinics for narcolepsy behavioral sleep medicine and sleep surgery in 2009 the stanford sleep disorders clinic moved to a state of the art facility in the new stanford medicine outpatient center in redwood city see maps and directions the sleep clinic has 14 clinical beds four additional beds dedicated to research and treats more than 5000 adults and children each year including patients from all over the world the clinic also has a fully accredited by the american academy of sleep medicine and has an acgme accredited sleep medicine fellowship program learn more click on the links below to learn more about the world renowned stanford sleep disorders clinic planning your visit to the sleep clinic tests for sleep disorders treatments for sleep disorders acgme accredited sleep medicine fellowship program you are here stanford medicine school of medicine departments the stanford center for sleep sciences and medicine clinical program navigation for this section clinical program home research programs clinical program sleep disorders educational programs about us site navigation home research programs clinical program sleep disorders educational programs about us overview contact us maps and directions our team people alumni of the sl